        "timestamp": "2020-04-16 05:12:43.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2\n\nRupinderjeet Singh, thanks for the contributions.\nI will not merge these changes, for bringing a very limited value. \n\nAlthough Sonar alerts for the proposed changes, I think that:\n1) Changing auto-generated equals() methods has no benefit, as equals() has it own special conventions.\n2) An if block should be enclosed in a curly braces. Where a single \"then\" statement is given, there are two options: blocking it with curly braces is better than having it in the same line of the if.\nAnyhow, putting in a seperate line without braces is mostly not an accepted practice.",
